        <argsstring>[CONFIG_LED_MATRIX_ROWS *CONFIG_LED_MATRIX_COLUMNS]</argsstring>
        <name>led_matrix_map</name>
        <initializer>= {
     0,  1,  2,  3,  4,  5,
    10, 11, 12, 13, 14, 15,
    20, 21, 22, 23,  8,  9,
    30, 31, 16, 17, 18, 19,
    24, 25, 26, 27, 28, 29
}</initializer>
        <briefdescription>
<para>A mapping of the logical indexes of the LED matrix to the actual physical configuration of the LEDs, start from the bottom left. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This mapping starts from the bottom left of the matrix and defines how each logical LED index corresponds to the physical wiring of the LED matrix</para>
<para>Default SRA Board LED matrix mappings (change for future versions, current version : v2.7)</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>This mapping starts from the bottom left of the matrix and the next logical index corresponds to the LED to the right in the same row. If the LED happens to be the last one in the row then the index corresponds to the first LED in the next (upper) row </para>
</simplesect>
<simplesect kind="note"><para>For the v2.7 mapping pins outputs 6 and 7 are not connected to any LEDs and do not have any effect on the final pattern of the LEDs. (Remove or update this note in later versions) </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
